#Text=Stay Organized in College
#Text=Organization is not only keeping your notes in order , it is much more than that .
#Text=Follow these steps to help you stay organized in college .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Get yourself a planner .
#Text=Managing your time in college is the most important thing you can do .
#Text=Buy yourself a daily , weekly , or even monthly planner .
#Text=This small investment will move mountains as you progress towards a successful college career .
#Text=Track down exam dates .
#Text=Working backward is the best way to go about planning your next semester .
#Text=Sit down with all your class syllabuses and highlight all final and midterm exam dates .
#Text=These will be the first thing you will want to write down in your newly purchased planner . 路 Doing this you will see potential hazards with overlapping exams and assignments
#Text=Find quizzes and assignments .
#Text=Collecting quizzes and assignments dates must follow finding exam dates .
#Text=These lower percentage assignments may seem unimportant but they add up .
#Text=Finding these dates may require more work than simply looking at the syllabus .
#Text=You may have to talk to your professor or teaching assistant to find out when homework , projects and quizzes are .
#Text=Never forget important information .
#Text=On the cover of your planner write down all your professors and teaching assistants office hours as well as grade breakdowns for each class .
#Text=There is nothing worse than finding out that the assignment you ignored was worth more than you expected .
#Text=This information will allow you to stay aligned in each class and force yourself to participate more therefore keeping up with each class .
#Text=One notebook for each class .
#Text=Purchasing a notebook for each class may seem like a waste of money and weight to slug around but it has been proven to boost grades therefore organization .
#Text=Only write down notes in the proper notebook and you will never be sent hunting for something again .
#Text=All loose sleeve papers and handouts go inside as well .
#Text=On the cover write down exam dates , due dates , office hours and grade break downs for that specific class .
#Text=Befriend your professors and teaching assistants .
#Text=Communication is key .
#Text=Speaking to your professor one on one is crucial .
#Text=It is impossible to be organized in a class that you are unaware what is going on .
#Text=Your professor and teaching assistant are getting paid to serve you as a student .
#Text=Set up a meeting with both outside of class where you can explain your strengths and weaknesses to them and ask how you think the best way to be successful is .
#Text=Ask them anything that comes to mind .
#Text=After this meeting write all of it down and review it .
#Text=Depict what they said and run with it .
#Text=Their little tricks and tells will dramatically help you in their class and being a student in general .
#Text=Do not work around work .
#Text=Speaking to your manager is something that should be done at the beginning of every semester .
#Text=Grab your planner and walk through your manager what you are about to go through for school .
#Text=Tell them your important dates that you will need time off before to properly prepare .
#Text=Not all jobs are east going so this is your best bet on balancing school and work .
#Text=At the end of explaining your next couple months to your manager ask them if it is possible to get your schedule as early as possible .
#Text=Having a set schedule will allow you to look ahead and know what you will have to do to keep your busy schedule alive .
#Text=Set time to breath .
#Text=Breathing easy may just keep you alive in college .
#Text=Becoming overwhelmed is a very common thing to happen during sometime during your hectic semester .
#Text=Setting time aside for yourself will give you the chance to not worry about school , work , social etc. and just focus on you for a change .
#Text=Allowing yourself to catch up to your normal will avoid being overwhelmed and keeping you on schedule .
#Text=This will keep you organized .
#Text=This will keep you going . 路 Time to yourself could include : Working out , yoga , reading , etc.
#Text=Calendars .
#Text=Looking ahead is one of the main things to stay organization in college .
#Text=Aside from the planner which will be used on the go and at school .
#Text=Setting up calendars at your home study area can play a major role in organization .
#Text=Buy or print off 4-5 months ahead .
#Text=Write down exam dates , project dates and your work schedule .
#Text=Then post these pieces in front of where you study at home .
#Text=The constant reminder as you sit and do your work every night will help remind you of what is coming ahead .
#Text=This will force yourself to get a jump on assignments and projects .
#Text=Review planner daily .
#Text=Reviewing your planner will keep yourself in your own loop .
#Text=Your planner is your life line .
#Text=It has all your information for a successful semester .
#Text=Setting aside 5-10 minutes a day to review your own planner will remind you of dates and push yourself to tackle assignments earlier .
#Text=It will also jolt new things to write down like social activities that will alter your regular schedule .
#Text=Color coordinate everything .
#Text=Studying your notes is boring enough , so spice it up a bit and make it more appealing .
#Text=Add in some color .
#Text=Underline your titles and highlight key words .
#Text=This is a proven useful tactic to stay organize .
#Text=The science behind it is when you come back to your notes you can identify the information on the paper more easily .
#Text=Seeing an arrange of colors will spark a memory quicker than reading the first paragraph .
#Text=Looking for key words that are highlighted will also save time and give you a better jump on the new material .
#Text=Make a to-do list .
#Text=Creating a to-do list will break down your larger goals into much smaller , more accomplishable goals .
#Text=These lists can be on your phone , laptop or even old fashion and pen and paper .
#Text=On this list , you want to write down things to do in the next week .
#Text=Start by writing down larger goals and then break it down into smaller maybe even hourly goals .
#Text=Having a to-do list will keep you on track to complete all things expected .
#Text=Try and complete each task rather move them around as they will bunch up quickly and some will eventually be passed on .
